[SN]TITLE[SN]
Fire crews discover body after Ceredigion farmhouse blaze

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
An investigation is under way after a body was discovered at a Ceredigion farmhouse following a fire.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Emergency services were called to the property in Abermagwr, about seven miles (11km) east of Aberystwyth, just after 10:30 GMT on Wednesday.
A body was found inside the property after the fire was put out.
Mid and West Wales Fire and Rescue Service said it was investigating in collaboration with Dyfed-Powys Police.
Police said the deceased's next of kin and the coroner had been informed of the incident.
